SIMPLE: equalize
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Equalize
<hw>E"qual*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Equalized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Equalizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧galiser</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make equal; to
cause to correspond, or be like, in amount or degree as compared;
<as>as, to <ex>equalize</ex> accounts, burdens, or taxes</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One poor moment can suffice⟦br⟧
To <qex>equalize</qex> the lofty and the low.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No system of instruction will completely <qex>equalize</qex>
natural powers.</q> <rj><qau>Whately.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To pronounce equal; to compare as equal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Which we <qex>equalize</qex>, and perhaps would willingly prefer
to the Iliad.</q> <rj><qau>Orrery.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To be equal to; equal; to match.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It could not <qex>equalize</qex> the hundredth part⟦br⟧
Of what her eyes have kindled in my heart.</q>
<rj><qau>Waller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Equalizing bar</b></col> <fld>(Railroad Mach.)</fld>,
<cd>a lever connecting two axle boxes, or two springs in a car truck or
locomotive, to equalize the pressure on the axles.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Equalizer</ent>⟦br⟧
